data.content:
Here's what changes for each item in .NET 10:

---

### 1. `WebHostBuilder` → `WebApplication.CreateBuilder()`
The legacy `WebHost.CreateDefaultBuilder()` hosting model is **removed**. Migrate to the minimal hosting model:

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
var host = WebHost.CreateDefaultBuilder(args)
    .UseStartup<Startup>()
    .Build();
host.Run();

// After (.NET 10)
var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);
// Move Startup.ConfigureServices() content here
var app = builder.Build();
// Move Startup.Configure() content here
app.Run();
```

---

### 2. `.WithOpenApi()` removed
The `WithOpenApi()` extension on minimal API endpoints is **removed**. OpenAPI metadata is now discovered automatically by the built-in pipeline:

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
app.MapGet("/items", () => ...).WithOpenApi();

// After (.NET 10) — just remove the call; metadata is inferred
builder.Services.AddOpenApi();
// ...
app.MapOpenApi();
app.MapGet("/items", () => ...);
```

---

### 3. `<IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers>` removed
The `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Api.Analyzers` package and its MSBuild property are **removed**. The SDK now includes equivalent analyzers by default — just delete the property:

```xml
<!-- Remove this line from your .csproj -->
<IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers>true</IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers>
```

---

### 4. `Microsoft.Extensions.ApiDescription.Client` (NSwag)
`ApiDescription.Server` (the build-time doc generator that feeds NSwag) is **deprecated** in favor of the built-in `AddOpenApi()`/`MapOpenApi()` pipeline. For client generation, switch to generating against the runtime endpoint or a saved JSON file:

```xml
<!-- Remove the old Server package reference -->
<!-- Keep ApiDescription.Client if you still use NSwag/NSwag.MSBuild -->
<!-- Point NSwag at the /openapi/v1.json endpoint or a file exported via: -->
<!-- dotnet run -- --urls http://localhost:5000 & curl .../openapi/v1.json > api.json -->
```

---

### 5. `IActionContextAccessor` as singleton
Singleton registration is **no longer allowed** — the service uses `AsyncLocal<>` internally and the framework now enforces **scoped** lifetime:

```csharp
// Before
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IActionContextAccessor, ActionContextAccessor>();

// After
builder.Services.AddHttpContextAccessor(); // already scoped
builder.Services.AddScoped<IActionContextAccessor, ActionContextAccessor>();
```

---

### 6. `IPNetwork` type replaced
`Microsoft.AspNetCore.HttpOverrides.IPNetwork` is **removed**. Use the BCL type `System.Net.IPNetwork` (available since .NET 8):

```csharp
// Before (.NET 9)
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.HttpOverrides;
options.KnownNetworks.Add(new IPNetwork(IPAddress.Parse("10.0.0.0"), 8));

// After (.NET 10)
using System.Net;
options.KnownNetworks.Add(new IPNetwork(IPAddress.Parse("10.0.0.0"), 8));
```

The constructor signature is the same — only the `using` changes.

---

### 7. `AddRazorRuntimeCompilation()` removed
The `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc.Razor.RuntimeCompilation` package is **removed entirely**. Use `dotnet watch` for dev-time hot reload instead:

```bash
# Replace runtime compilation with:
dotnet watch run
```

Remove the package reference and the `AddRazorRuntimeCompilation()` call.

---

### 8. 401 redirect → proper status codes for APIs
Cookie authentication no longer redirects API requests to the login page. .NET 10 **defaults to returning 401/403 status codes** when the request indicates an API client (e.g., `Accept: application/json`, or no `text/html`). If you had workarounds like custom `OnRedirectToLogin`, you can simplify:

```csharp
// Before — manual workaround
options.Events.OnRedirectToLogin = ctx =>
{
    ctx.Response.StatusCode = 401;
    return Task.CompletedTask;
};

// After — the default behavior is correct for APIs; remove the workaround
builder.Services.AddAuthentication()
    .AddCookie();
```

---

**Summary checklist:**

| Area | Action |
|---|---|
| Hosting model | Rewrite to `WebApplication.CreateBuilder()` |
| `.WithOpenApi()` | Delete calls |
| OpenAPI analyzers | Remove `<IncludeOpenApiAnalyzers>` property |
| NSwag pipeline | Point at built-in `/openapi/v1.json` endpoint |
| `IActionContextAccessor` | Change to `AddScoped` |
| `IPNetwork` | Change `using` to `System.Net` |
| Razor runtime compilation | Remove package; use `dotnet watch` |
| 401 redirects | Remove custom redirect workarounds |
